						<p> Google search can find 3D models of animals, planets, astronauts, and even cells, and put these virtual models in a real environment. Now, Google has announced that it has launched a dinosaur model. Users use Google to search the corresponding dinosaur name on their mobile phones, and 3D models will appear in the search results, and then they can click the "view in 3D" button to view the 3D models. Google and Ludia's Jurassic world mobile game have brought 10 dinosaur models. Google said Ludia tried to make the model as realistic as possible. "Not only do we study from <a href="https://www.dinosaurjoy.com/google-search-adds-3d-dinosaur-model/">[...]</a></p>					</div>
