																<span class="vcard rich-snippet-hidden"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.dinosaurjoy.com/author/dinosaurjoy/" title="Posts by " rel="author"></a></span></span><span class="updated rich-snippet-hidden">2020-06-16T01:45:24+00:00</span>
												
					
					<div class="fusion-post-content-container">
						<p> Paleontologists at the National Center for science and technology in Buenos Aires, Argentina, have discovered a new species of dinosaur, a near bird, in Patagonia. According to infobae, the Argentine portal, the oborator chimentoi lived in modern Argentina about 90 million years ago during the Cretaceous period. The dinosaur is about 1.3 meters long and has a beautiful figure. The forelegs are like wings, very slender and beautiful; the hind legs are very suitable for running, with very sharp crescent claws. The research was published in the Journal of natural science. Photo of a new dinosaur species with winglike forelimbs <a href="https://www.dinosaurjoy.com/scientists-in-argentina-have-discovered-a-new-dinosaur-species-with-winglike-forelimbs/">[...]</a></p>					</div>
